A Westminster Magistrates Court in the United Kingdom has ruled that David Ukpo, the alleged victim in the organ harvesting case against former Deputy Senate President, Ike Ekweremadu, and his wife, Beatrice, is not 15 years old as initially claimed. Gavin Irwin, counsel for the Ekweremadus at Westminster Magistrates Court, London, insisted that the victim in the case, Ukpo is not a minor as the prosecutor claimed.  Irwin, while addressing the court on Thursday claimed that the victim has admitted that he is 21 years old as against the 15 years claimed by the prosecutor which could make the victim a minor.  "We deny that there was exploitation or intent to do so," Ekweremadu’s lawyer said. According to Arise TV, Ukpo admitted to the court that he is 21 years old and had been in the UK since February but did not present himself to the police till May. The couple who are currently being detained in different prisons in the UK over alleged organ harvesting and trafficking appeared in the UK Court on Thursday for continued trial. See Also






