3 Days Ago But while it is not yet clear whether the information was eventually sent to London before the Thursday court proceedings, Ekweremadu’s counsel claimed that the victim has admitted that he is 21 years old, but the prosecutor objected to the claim. However, the court ruled that the victim is not a minor, hence, Ukpo will no longer be considered a minor in the trial.  Meanwhile, the case has been adjourned to August 4 and the Ekweremadus will appear at the Central Criminal Court in London for the continuation of the trial as approved by the UK Attorney General.  Present at the Westminster Magistrates Court from Nigeria were former Senate Minority Leader, Senator Enyinnaya Abaribe; former Senate President, David Mark; former Minister of State for Education, Chukwuemeka Nwajiuba and Chairman of the Senate Committee on Foreign Affairs, Adamu Bulkachuwa.  